A lecturer at the Federal University, Dutsinma,  Katsina, Abubakar Idris, has been abducted by hoodlums on Friday. He was abducted in his residence at No. 41A Lawal Aliyu Road, Barnawa area in Kaduna metropolis. Powered by RubiQube Ad Network The Kaduna State Police Command Public Relations Officer, DSP Yakubu Sabo confirmed the incident to News Agency of Nigeria (NAN) on Saturday. Sabo said the command received information through the Divisional Police Officer (DPO), Barnawa Division, Kaduna, that two unidentified persons gained entrance into Idris’ residence. “The unidentified men forced him to enter his ash-coloured BMW car with Registration number not yet known, and zoomed off to an unknown destination,” he said. Sabo added that patrol teams led by the DPO quickly moved to the scene but the hoodlums had escaped with the victim. He said investigation later revealed that the victim was trailed by the hoodlums while returning home at about 1am. “The Command is currently making efforts to apprehend the fleeing suspected criminals and rescue the victim,” he said.